# Deprecated — use AGENTS.md and .cursor/rules/*.mdc instead.
#
# This file remains for tools that only read .cursorrules at the repo root.
# Canonical instructions: AGENTS.md → .docs/prompting/AI_GUARDRAILS.md

Read AGENTS.md before making changes.

- Documentation in `.docs/` is authoritative. Push back on requests that contradict it, or get explicit permission and update docs.
- Code must be readable, cohesive, and validated (`pnpm run validate`, `pnpm run test`).
- Happy-path tests by default; no test theater.
- UX wins over convenience. Reject anti-UX requests with a better alternative.
- Use tools and subagents when they clearly help, not reflexively.
